'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently `fr-CA` is not yet supported by Composite so will read Contoso `fr-CA` override string, but fallback Composite to `fr`)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Automatically detect OS language if OS language is supported by Contoso app localization and supported by Composite
  1. Will check languageCode ll-CC (language-region) if supported
  2. If ll-CC not supported, fall back to check languageCode ll (language) if supported
  3. Default language is `en` (English)
* When specified languageCode in `LocalizationConfiguration` will override the auto detected OS language
* Added localization for Demo app with languages: `en`, `zh-Hant`, `fr`, `fr-CA` (currently fr-CA is not yet supported by Composite)

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Switch system OS language to French or Traditional Chinese, then open the app, go too `Settings` page select `Language` as `auto` (Detect OS locale)
* Should see `Join Call` label in setup screen to show `Join Call (override <language>)` for French and Traditional Chinese because both Contoso (Demo app) and Composite supports French and Traditional Chinese

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Public facing api for Localization
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with customStrings
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with locale and custom localizable.strings file name
  * Get default supported languages
  * Get predefined localization strings for support language, if unsupported language is provided will return empty dictionary * Remove locale in compliance banner URL, will redirect to appropriate language based on user's browser language

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature

[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Test when providing a unsupported language in LocalizationConfiguration will log warning message
* Can use static method to get supported languages
* Can use static method to get predefined key-value strings for supported languages
* Switch to a different language on device and test Teams call with recording/transcription, and click on `Learn more` or `Privacy Policy` will open website to system/browser language

## Other Information

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Public facing api for Localization
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with customStrings
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with locale and custom localizable.strings file name
  * Get default supported languages
  * Get predefined localization strings for support language, if unsupported language is provided will return empty dictionary * Remove locale in compliance banner URL, will redirect to appropriate language based on user's browser language

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Test when providing a unsupported language in LocalizationConfiguration will log warning message
* Can use static method to get supported languages
* Can use static method to get predefined key-value strings for supported languages
* Switch to a different language on device and test Teams call with recording/transcription, and click on `Learn more` or `Privacy Policy` will open website to system/browser language

## Other Information
<!-- Add any other helpful information that may be needed here. -->

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Public facing api for Localization
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with customStrings
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with locale and custom localizable.strings file name
  * Get default supported languages
  * Get predefined localization strings for support language, if unsupported language is provided will return empty dictionary * Remove locale in compliance banner URL, will redirect to appropriate language based on user's browser language

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Test when providing a unsupported language in LocalizationConfiguration will log warning message
* Can use static method to get supported languages
* Can use static method to get predefined key-value strings for supported languages
* Switch to a different language on device and test Teams call with recording/transcription, and click on `Learn more` or `Privacy Policy` will open website to system/browser language

## Other Information
<!-- Add any other helpful information that may be needed here. -->

'body': '## Purpose
<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Public facing api for Localization
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with customStrings
  * Initialize LocalizationConfiguration with locale and custom localizable.strings file name
  * Get default supported languages
  * Get predefined localization strings for support language, if unsupported language is provided will return empty dictionary * Remove locale in compliance banner URL, will redirect to appropriate language based on user's browser language

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[ x ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

<!-- Please check the one that applies to this PR using "x". -->
```
[ ] Bugfix
[ x ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[ ] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Test when providing a unsupported language in LocalizationConfiguration will log warning message
* Can use static method to get supported languages
* Can use static method to get predefined key-value strings for supported languages
* Switch to a different language on device and test Teams call with recording/transcription, and click on `Learn more` or `Privacy Policy` will open website to system/browser language

## Other Information
<!-- Add any other helpful information that may be needed here. -->

In this PR I drafted the feature supporting user pinch, zoom and pan gestures in video screen share in a call. The functionalities resembles the MS Teams application UX.
Additional features introduced:
* double tap to zoom in / zoom out
* only zooming the actual video content, not the entire rendered view from SDK
* Improved screen share video quality in iPhone.

* double tap to zoom in / zoom out
* only zooming the actual video content, not the entire rendered view from SDK
* Improved screen share video quality in iPhone.

Additional features introduced:
* double tap to zoom in / zoom out
* only zooming the actual video content, not the entire rendered view from SDK
* Improved screen share video quality in iPhone.

```

git checkout [branch-name]

```

* Join a call either using group or Teams call, in iOS app and Teams application (desktop)

* Follow **What to Check section**

* Improved screen share video quality in iPhone.

* Improved screen share video quality in iPhone.
